{
  "stem": "95.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And if he did-- could make a living, I would never have gone through the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I would have been in Argentina right now, speaking Spanish instead of English or French.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Obviously, it did not-- it did not work out in Argentina, and he went right back to Poland.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "In 1921, my grandfather received a letter from the French government saying that one of his sons who lived in France died during World War I, and they should send somebody to France to find out what to do with his body and everything.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So my grandfather sent, again, my father with his younger brother to Paris, France in 1921.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I guess they took care of his body.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But somehow, he found a distant cousin there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And somehow, the life was such a contrast between Warsaw and Paris that he stayed there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And I-- I laugh about it, and it's really not laughable, but most men did the same thing.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "When they immigrated to different countries, to new countries, they all went by themselves, thinking, if I can make a living, I will send for my family.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And most of them had lots of children.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And I always said, I don't know how these women, who stayed in their native country with all these children, survived waiting for their husband to say, come over.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "It's fine now.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "It took two years for my father to decide, I'm not going to go back to Poland.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "He never did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "In 1923, he told my mother to just grab all the children and come to France.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And a lot of my sisters-- half sisters were already married.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Some of them stayed in-- in Poland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "But the rest of my family went-- immigrated to France in 1923.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
